<div class="govuk-grid-row">
    <div class="govuk-grid-column-full">
        <h2 class="govuk-heading-l">Design consistently</h2>
    </div>
    <div class="govuk-grid-column-two-thirds">
        <p>Everything you are looking to design has probably already been designed elsewhere already, so make use of existing patterns and components.</p>
        <p>You should aim to design to established, industry best practices - users spend most of their time on other sites, so users will expect our services to work the same way as other sites they already use. </p>
        <p>Using and improving existing GOV.UK Design System components, enables you to create services which will feel familiar to users who use other government services.</p>
        <p>When designs behave the same, users won't have to learn something new, they know what to expect based on a familiar experience. Users will trust a service that feels familiar, even if what they are doing is nothing like another service or task they do elsewhere.</p>

