<div class="govuk-grid-row">
    <div class="govuk-grid-column-full">
        <h2 class="govuk-heading-l">Design for less</h2>
    </div>
    <div class="govuk-grid-column-two-thirds">
        <p>Start designing with just content. Iterate design to make it more usability, not more complex.</p>
        <p>Overloading a page with components and different elements, can make it overwhelming and cause cognitive overload. Make best use of whitespace and headers to make things easier to understand, navigate and use. </p>
        <p>Some things in design are functional, others purely aesthetic. If they aren't adding to the overall experience, then remove it - reduce the design to the necessary features for the user to complete their task.</p>
        <p>When writing content, write only what you need to. Make the main thing on a page, the most important thing the user needs to do or understand.</p>
    </div>
