<div class="govuk-grid-row">
    <div class="govuk-grid-column-full">
        <h2 class="govuk-heading-l">Make it efficient</h2>
    </div>
    <div class="govuk-grid-column-two-thirds">
        <p>The best user experience comes from services that react quickly, prevent mistakes and enable users to do what they need to, quickly.</p>
        <p>Friction in services makes things harder to use, understand and cause frustration.</p>
        <p>Think about how your design works for different user groups. Some users may be novice so need extra help, others proficient. Can you give users shortcuts to make their use of the same service easier?</p>
        <p>Avoid making service interactions complicated, its better to spread a process out over multiple pages rather than put a lot of things on one page.</p>
        <p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/guidance/government-design-principles#do-the-hard-work-to-make-it-simple" target="_blank">Do the hard work to make it simple</a>. This applies for the user's benefit, but also iterating design and content. Its much easier to change a simple page, than one that has lots of elements or logic on it, or where it appears in a journey.</p>
    </div>
